renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

resetClass(uint256).details: Remove all token ids for a given class, causing it to fall back to creating/minting into the nft address

setClassForTokenId(uint256,uint256).details: If the tokens for some class are pre-minted and owned by the contract owner, they can be used for a given class by setting them here

setOptionSettings(uint8,uint256,uint16[6.details: Set the settings for a particular lootbox option

params._classProbabilities: Array of probabilities (basis points, so integers out of 10,000)                           of receiving each class (the index in the array).                           Should add up to 10k and be descending in value.
params._guarantees: Array of the number of guaranteed items received for each class                           (the index in the array).
params._maxQuantityPerOpen: Maximum number of items to mint per open.                           Set to 0 to disable this option.
params._option: The Option to set settings for

setSeed(uint256).details: Improve pseudorandom number generator by letting the owner set the seed manually, making attacks more difficult

params._newSeed: The new seed to use for the next transaction

setTokenIdsForClass(uint8,uint256[]).details: Alternate way to add token ids to a class Note: resets the full list for the class instead of adding each token id

setTokenIdsForClasses(uint256[6]).details: Set token IDs for each rarity class. Bulk version of `setTokenIdForClass`

params._tokenIds: List of token IDs to set for each class, specified above in order

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Called by a pauser to unpause, returns to normal state.

devdoc.title: MyLootBox MyLootBox - a randomized and openable lootbox of MyCollectibles

balanceOf(address,uint256).notice: Get the factory's ownership of Option. Should be the amount it can still mint. NOTE: Called by `canMint`

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Hack to get things to work automatically on OpenSea. Use safeTransferFrom so the frontend doesn't have to worry about different method names.
